FT  25 AUG 94 / Council's police force plan criticised
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALAN PIKE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Plans by Conservative-controlled Wandsworth council in London to establish a
municipal police force to patrol housing estates were criticised yesterday
by police organisations.
The council is considering extending its parks police patrols to estates,
using council staff sworn in by magistrates as constables and exercising
powers of arrest.
Mr Edward Lister, council leader, said on BBC Radio yesterday that problems
