FT  25 AUG 94 / Channel island sale price halved
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Lihou Island, the smallest inhabited Channel island, which failed to find a
buyer when it was offered for sale at Pounds 1m two years ago, is back on
the market at Pounds 500,000.
Lihou is a mile off the south-west coast of Guernsey, to which it is linked
by a causeway during low spring tides. Its 40 acres include the ruins of a
12th century Benedictine priory.
