FT  24 AUG 94 / Delays found in London tax appeals
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
More than half of all appeals against council tax bandings in Greater London
had still not been resolved 16 months after the tax was introduced, a survey
by the Labour-controlled Association of London Authorities has found.
At the end of July 57.2 per cent of appeals across London were outstanding.
Hounslow and Barking and Dagenham were the only boroughs to have resolved
more than half of their appeals.
The boroughs with the highest proportions of appeals outstanding were Bexley
(66.3 per cent), Tower Hamlets (66 per cent) and Lambeth (65.9 per cent).
