FT  24 AUG 94 / Albania protests about Greece
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TIRANA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Albania urged the US and the Nato alliance yesterday to press Greece to stop
'provocative acts'. This marks a further deterioration in relations between
the two Balkan neighbours, at odds over the ethnic Greek minority in
Albania. President Sali Berisha recalled Albania's envoy from Athens on
Monday as a protest, after a Greek aircraft flew over Albanian territory
dropping leaflets calling for the overthrow of the Tirana government.
Albania brushed aside Greece's explanation that the flight was an act of a
renegade aviator who stole a crop-duster, and has accused Athens of
launching a 'Cold War' against Tirana. Tensions have risen since the trial
for spying of five ethnic Greeks opened in Tirana this month. Greece says
the trial is aimed at intimidating Albania's Greek minority.
