</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Pakistan has the atomic bomb, opposition leader and former prime minister
Nawaz Sharif (left) admitted. The private PPI news agency reported him as
confirming the fact at a rally in the Pakistani-controlled part of Kashmir.
In the past, the country said it had the capability to make nuclear weapons
but had decided as a matter of policy not to make them. Some officials said
Mr Sharif's statement could be meant to embarrass the government on home and
foreign policy fronts.
</TEXT>
