FT  23 AUG 94 / UK Company News: Aerospace Engineering 71% ahead
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Aerospace Engineering, the precision engineering group, lifted pre-tax
profits by 71 per cent from Pounds 214,000 to Pounds 367,000 during the year
to April 30.
Mr John Davis, chairman and chief executive, said the group was benefiting
from the rationalisation programme completed last year. The balance sheet
was strengthened, he added, following the sale of a surplus property in
Swindon.
There was improved demand for printed circuit boards and the group expected
microwave board demand to continue growing.
Turnover of continuing activities slipped to Pounds 15.7m (Pounds 17.6m).
Earnings per share rose from 0.25p to 0.64p and the dividend is held at
0.75p with an unchanged final of 0.5p.
